From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: c127dev <contact@c127.dev>
Date: Mon, 9 Mar 2026 07:22:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] net: dwc_eth_qos: Add support for Motorcomm YT6801

This patch adds a new glue driver for the Motorcomm YT6801 PCIe
Ethernet controller, which uses the Synopsys DesignWare Ethernet QOS
IP block (DWMAC4).

The driver includes support for:
- Mapping PCI BAR0 and adjusting for GMAC register offset.
- Reading the MAC address from the integrated eFuse. (Works on uboot)
- Proper reset and deassertion of the MDIO/PHY reset.
- Disabling OOB WOL for normal operation.

This work is based on the Linux kernel dwmac-motorcomm driver
authored by Yao Zi <me@ziyao.cc>.

Signed-off-by: c127dev <contact@c127.dev>
